//docs.nats.io/running-a-nats-service/configuration/securing_nats/auth_callout",children:"mapping for NATS"})," which handles language translation - encapsulating as a NATS message which may simplify this process."]}),"\n",(0,o.jsx)(n.li,{children:"Brooks then moves on to an example of using this in practice - check out the recording below for the full demo."}),"\n"]}),"\n",(0,o.jsx)(n.h3,{id:"discussion-automatic-pr-labeler--releaseyml-for-better-release-notes",children:"DISCUSSION: Automatic PR labeler + release.yml for better release notes"}),"\n",(0,o.jsxs)(n.ul,{children:["\n",(0,o.jsxs)(n.li,{children:["On the ",(0,o.jsx)(n.a,{href:"https://wasmcloud.com/docs/v1/roadmap/",children:"roadmap"}),"! We started looking into some of the ways we can improve our commit process."]}),"\n",(0,o.jsx)(n.li,{children:"When we open a PR, we write a conventional commit (scope etc, API, breaking change etc). What we have now, is a script in a github action that can auto-add labels to the PR regarding the type, scope and whether it is a breaking change)."}),"\n",(0,o.jsx)(n.li,{children:"All this culminates in an updated PR after the commit is validated. Afterwards, we look at the commits in the PR, scan them for impact (breaking, feature, CI etc)."}),"\n",(0,o.jsx)(n.li,{children:"We can also use this in github's automatic changelog feature to change the way the release notes are formatted. We can include or exclude certain labels, remove or add contribitors."}),"\n",(0,o.jsx)(n.li,{children:"This means we can exclude dependabot which removes complexity. We can also auto-organize our release notes."}),"\n",(0,o.jsx)(n.li,{children:"This is a really nice balance of being able to use conventional commits, and using some of the new functionality in github actions."}),"\n",(0,o.jsx)(n.li,{children:"This will make sure we are prioritizing breaking changes, and that they are easier to identify. We'll start to see the benefits in the next major provider SDK action."}),"\n",(0,o.jsx)(